        <p>Armenia is one of the world's oldest countries, with a rich history dating back to the 9th century BC. It was the first nation to adopt Christianity as its state religion in 301 AD.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="culture">
        <h2>Culture</h2>
        <p>Armenian culture is known for its unique language, music, dance, and cuisine. Traditional instruments like the duduk and dances such as the Yarkhushta are integral to Armenian identity.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="tourism">
        <h2>Tourism</h2>
        <p>Armenia offers stunning landscapes, from the majestic Mount Ararat to the serene Lake Sevan. Visitors can explore ancient monasteries, vibrant cities, and experience warm Armenian hospitality.</p>
